question: Will Adam Neumann buy back WeWork in February?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Adam Neumann or a company owned by Adam Neumann acquires WeWork between February 5 and February 29, 2024, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

For the purposes of this market, an announcement by Adam Neumann or his official representative, a company owned by Adam Neumann, or WeWork is enough to trigger a "Yes" resolution, regardless of whether the announced acquisition actually occurs. An announcement that a majority of its assets are being acquired suffices to resolve this market to "Yes."

Note: If an Adam Neumann owned company is part of the acquisition of the majority of WeWork's assets, it will suffice to resolve this market to "Yes" even if multiple other companies are involved. 

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from Adam Neumann or his official representative, a company owned by Adam Neumann, or WeWork, however a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

question: Will Warpcast break top 5 on the iOS App Store in February?
description:
Warpcast has been surging in the app store rankings, surpassing WeChat on Feb 4 (see https://twitter.com/dwr/status/1754378105836495168).

This market will resolve to "Yes" if Warpcast is in the top 5 free social networking iPhone apps at any point by February 29, 2024, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

The resolution source is the US iPhone App Store's "Top Free Apps" chart for the "Social Networking" category, viewable here: https://apps.apple.com/us/charts/iphone/social-networking-apps/6005?chart=top-free.

question: Will Solana Network go down again in February?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if the Solana Network experiences downtime for 30 minutes or longer between February 6, 12:00 PM ET, and February 29, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

If an outage starts before the end of this market's timeframe and extends past it, this market will resolve to "Yes" (e.g. if on February 29, 2024, at 11:45 PM ET an outage starts and lasts beyond March 1, 2024, 12:15 AM ET, this market will resolve to "Yes").

Downtime must occur for at least 30 minutes and be widely reported by a consensus of credible reporting. Sources such as https://solana.fm/blocks?cluster=mainnet-alpha, https://status.solana.com/uptime?page=5 and https://dune.com/dsaber/solana-network-health-report may additionally be considered.

question: Taylor Swift Super Bowl Parlay
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if at Super Bowl LVIII: Travis Kelce scores a touchdown, AND the Kansas City Chiefs win the game, AND Travis Kelce and Taylor Swift kiss while on venue grounds (must be confirmed by picture or video). Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

Note: A kiss on the cheek counts.

If Super Bowl LVIII is not completed by March 10, 2024, 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve 50-50.

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from the NFL and live footage from Super Bowl LVIII, however a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

question: Tucker Carlson + Putin interview released by Friday?
description:
On Feb 6, Tucker Carlson posted to X confirming that he was interviewing Putin (see https://twitter.com/TuckerCarlson/status/1754939251257475555).

This market will resolve to "Yes" if Tucker Carlson's interview with Vladimir Putin is released to the general public by February 9, 2024, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

Released previews of the interview won't count - the full interview must be released by the resolution date for this market to resolve to "Yes." 

The resolution source for this market will be footage of the interview and/or a consensus of credible reporting.
